alert.note: Alert for King (Washington) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Flood Warning issued November 05 at 11:57AM PDT until November 06 at 9:36AM PDT by NWS Seattle
info.description: ...The Flood Warning is extended for the following rivers in Washington... Snoqualmie River Near Carnation affecting King County. .Heavy rain over the area came to an end early Saturday morning with no hydrological significant rain forecast over the weekend. ...FLOOD WARNING NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL TOMORROW MORNING... * WHAT...Moderate flooding is occurring and moderate flooding is forecast. * WHERE...Snoqualmie River Near Carnation. * WHEN...Until tomorrow morning. * IMPACTS...At 56.0 feet, the Snoqualmie River will cause widespread flooding from Fall City downstream through Carnation and Duvall... inundating much of the farm land and numerous roads. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 11:30 AM PDT Saturday the stage was 56.9 feet. - Recent Activity...The maximum river stage in the 24 hours ending at 11:30 AM PDT Saturday was 56.9 feet. - Forecast...The river is expected to fall below flood stage late this evening. - Flood stage is 54.0 feet. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood &&
info.instruction: Motorists should not attempt to drive around barricades or drive cars through flooded areas. Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov. The next statement will be issued by this evening at 800 PM PDT.
